# Privacy Policy — Salesforce Data Model Chrome Extension

**Effective date:** 2026-03-19

This Privacy Policy describes how the **Salesforce Data Model** Chrome Extension (the "Extension") collects, uses, and protects information when you use it.

---

## 1. What the Extension Does

The Extension is a **read-only** Salesforce metadata browser that helps administrators and developers inspect the data model of any Salesforce org they are signed into. It provides:

- **Fields** — view field metadata (label, API name, type, required, unique, length, etc.) with clickable links to field setup pages.
- **Record Types** — list record types with assigned picklist value inspection.
- **Page Layouts** — list page layouts associated with an object.
- **FlexiPages** — list Lightning pages linked to an object.
- **Validation Rules** — view validation rule names, formulas, error messages, and active status.
- **Field Sets** — view field set members and descriptions.
- **Picklist Dependency Viewer** — visualize dependent picklist mappings in a matrix.
- **Excel Export** — export all of the above into a multi-sheet `.xls` workbook.

---

## 2. Information the Extension Accesses

### A. Salesforce Session Cookie (`sid`)

The Extension reads the Salesforce session cookie named **`sid`** for the Salesforce domain you are currently signed into. This cookie is:

- Used **only** to authenticate REST, Tooling, and Metadata API requests to **your own Salesforce org**.
- **Never** persisted in extension storage — it is read from Chrome's cookie store at runtime and held in memory only for the duration of the active session.
- **Never** transmitted to any server other than your Salesforce org.

### B. Salesforce Org Metadata

When you select an object, the Extension retrieves metadata through Salesforce APIs, including:

- Object describe information (fields, record types, picklist values).
- Tooling API metadata (`FieldDefinition`, `CustomField`, `EntityDefinition`, `FlexiPage`, `ValidationRule`, `Layout`, `FieldSet`).
- User identity information (your name and email as returned by Salesforce) for display in the header.

### C. Local Storage

The Extension uses `chrome.storage.local` and `chrome.storage.session` to persist:

- **Column configuration** — your preferred column order and visibility for each tab.
- **Tab configuration** — which tabs are visible.
- **Cached host/instance URL** — to reconnect to your org on subsequent opens (no tokens are stored).

No Salesforce data, field values, or record content is persisted.

---

## 3. How the Extension Uses Information

All accessed information is used **exclusively** to:

- Render the metadata browser UI inside the extension popup.
- Generate Excel export files that are downloaded directly to your device.
- Open Salesforce setup pages in new browser tabs when you click a link.

The Extension **does not** modify, create, update, or delete any data in your Salesforce org. It is strictly read-only.

---

## 4. Data Sharing and Selling

- The Extension does **not** sell, rent, or trade your personal information or Salesforce data.
- The Extension does **not** share data with third parties, analytics services, or advertising networks.
- The Extension does **not** transmit any data to external servers controlled by the developer.

The Extension communicates **only** with your Salesforce org domains:

- `*.salesforce.com`
- `*.force.com`
- `*.salesforce-setup.com`
- `*.visualforce.com`
- `*.lightning.force.com`
- `*.my.salesforce.com`

---

## 5. Data Storage and Retention

- **Session tokens** are never written to extension storage. The `sid` cookie is read from Chrome's cookie store on demand.
- **Metadata** fetched from Salesforce is held in memory only while the extension popup is open. Closing the popup discards all fetched metadata.
- **Preferences** (column/tab configuration) are stored locally in your browser profile and can be reset from the Settings page at any time.

---

## 6. Permissions Justification

| Permission | Reason |
|---|---|
| `cookies` | Read the Salesforce `sid` session cookie for API authentication. |
| `storage` | Persist user preferences (column order, tab visibility). |
| `tabs` | Open Salesforce setup pages and the extension popup in new tabs. |
| `windows` | Not actively used (retained for compatibility). |
| Host permissions (`*.salesforce.com`, etc.) | Required to make API requests to Salesforce endpoints. |

---

## 7. Security

The Extension follows security best practices:

- **Manifest V3** — uses a service worker with no persistent background page.
- **Least-privilege permissions** — only the minimum required permissions are declared.
- **No `web_accessible_resources`** — extension resources are not exposed to web pages.
- **No `innerHTML`** — all DOM rendering uses safe APIs (`textContent`, `createElement`) to prevent XSS.
- **No token persistence** — session tokens are never written to storage.

You are responsible for:

- Controlling access to your Chrome profile.
- Ensuring appropriate Salesforce permissions are assigned to your user account.

---

## 8. Your Choices

You can:

- **Remove the Extension** at any time from `chrome://extensions`.
- **Reset preferences** from the Settings page to clear stored column/tab configuration.
- **Revoke Salesforce access** by logging out of Salesforce, which invalidates the session cookie.

---

## 9. Children's Privacy

The Extension is not directed to children under 13 and is not intended for use by minors.

